Navigate to Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Policies &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; VMware View Agent Configuration &gt;&gt; Agent Configuration. Double-click the "CommandsToRunOnConnect" setting.

If "CommandsToRunOnConnect" is "Not Configured" or "Disabled", this is not a finding.

Click the "Show..." button next to "Commands". If any of the listed commands are not expected, approved, and required, this is a finding.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA></STIG_DATA><STIG_DATA><VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Fix_Text</VULN_ATTRIBUTE><ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Ensure the vdm_agent*.admx templates are added. Open the "Group Policy Management" MMC snap-in. Open the site-specific GPO applying Horizon settings to the VDI desktops or RDS hosts.

Navigate to Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Policies &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; VMware View Agent Configuration &gt;&gt; Agent Configuration. Double-click the "CommandsToRunOnConnect" setting.

Option 1:

Click the radio button next to "Disabled". Click "OK".

Option 2:

Make sure the setting is "Enabled".

